 valign=top bgcolor=#FF9933 class=headings><font color=#330066>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/utwullie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>twullie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mewling</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/23/02 2:21:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2424.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ambidexterity hmm</span><hr size=1> Anyone who have this AA Skill?<br>How much of a diference did it do?<br><br>I'm unsure of if this is worth the 9 AA xp points, not that there is much else to choose from but if it's only marginally it wont be that high in priority.<br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=172691" target="_blank">~ Gaturbarsher Savage Lord of Caer Cadarn @ Vazaelle ~</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ukubientp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KubienTP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Predator</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/23/02 3:34:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2424.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ambidexterity hmm</span><hr size=1> Not too much useful information here sense its not reliable, but I thought I heard somewhere that a monk who trained Ambidexterity had a dps increase of something around 10-15%.  I think if you realy look closly you dont actauly, even with high dual wield skill, swing your offhand weapon very offten.<br><br>While im not very sure, but from my observations, everytime you swing your primary hand your offhand has a chance to swing that is actualy suprisingly low with maxed out dual wield skill.  Some will argue that the off hand swings independent of primary hand but even with a very high delay weapon in primary and low delay weapon in offhand (for testing this), checking through logs I did not once see offhand swing before primary. <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=263127">Kubien Soulleaf</a> Bard ~Retierd~<br><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=224621">Koramorf Iznoshammy</a> Beastlord ~Retierd~<br><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=261142">Bindolur</a> Warrior ~Retierd~<br><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=298147">Kinael</a> Necromancer ~Retierd~<br><a target="new" href=" http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=281419">Rarkorle</a> Monk ~Retierd~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/usilkysong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silkysong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/23/02 3:53:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2424.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ambidexterity hmm</span><hr size=1> Dual wielding works like this...<br><br>First, your primary and secondary hands swing entirely independently. Each has it's own delay based time. <br><br>Every time your primary hand timer goes off you swing. <br><br>Every time your secondary timer goes off, you make a roll based on your Dual Wield skill. If you make the roll, you swing.<br><br>Simple. Ambidexterity improves the chance to make your Dual Wield skill roll (effectively giving you a higher skill in Dual Wield.) <p><br><br><img src="http://www.intelligamer.com/kerbe/unrulysig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/usoulshysoulshade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SoulshySoulshade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/24/02 6:02:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2424.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ambidexterity hmm</span><hr size=1> Have recently gained this class skill and the hit ratio is noticeable. After speaking with a few Monks about the skill most consider Ambidex to increase overall DPS by roughly 7 percent.<br><br>Soulshy Soulshade <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/usoulshysoulshade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SoulshySoulshade</A> at: 7/24/02 6:03:39 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/udannorstoutwise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dannor Stoutwise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#871F78>(7/24/02 6:30:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2424.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ambidexterity hmm</span><hr size=1> Its very easy to test. Grab a stein of take-your-pick in your primary hand, kill pet and find a green mob. Kill it with only your secondary weapon. Works like a charm, well if you got a bad skill in Dual Wield it will not swing very often. Get a shiny stone dagger for your secondary until you get your skill up. (cheap weapon that has 19 in delay..)<br><br>For my lvl 33 beastlord he swings secondary weapon about half as often as primary. Probably a bit less, but not with very much.<br><br>Try turning your misses on if your interested in how often you actually swing the weapon though. <p><div align="center"><img src=http://member.isavvix.com/cyberwarlock/images/EQ/DannorStoutwise.jpg border=0 width=325 height=164></div></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2424.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2424.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2424.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.brentcopeland.com/beastlord/images/messageboard/BL_add_reply2.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=2424.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.threadControl?topicID=2424.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2424.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2424.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub115.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqbeastlordfrm1">The Den<option value="eqbeastlordfrm2">General Spell Discussion<